<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A founding member of Australian rock band Skyhooks has died after falling off a ladder.</p>

<p>Peter Starkie, the original guitarist of the 1970s glam rock band, died on Sunday, he was aged 72.</p>

<p>His brother Bob, who replaced him in the band, shared the tragic news on Facebook, saying his brother had died in 'one of those stupid ladder accidents'.</p>

<p>In his heartfelt tribute, he opened up about admiring his brother who was a 'fabulous guitarist'.</p>

<p>'Quite honestly this is just a f***ing tragedy especially for Dianna and the girls. (and in lockdown!)</p>

<p>'So one and all, as my mother would say, ''count your Blessing''.' </p>

<p>Skyhooks shot to fame in the mid-70s with hits such as Horror Movie, Ego is Not A Dirty Word, All My Friends Are Getting Married and Women In Uniform.</p>

<p>The band stopped regularly playing when Strachan died in a helicopter accident at Noosa in 2001. </p>

<p>Many fans have been left shocked by Peter's sudden death, leaving heartfelt tributes on the band's Facebook page.</p>

<p>'Shocked and saddened at this news. Condolences to you and the families,' one person wrote. </p>

<p>'My Iove and condolences to you Bob and all your family...may Peter RIP always,' another wrote.</p>

<p>'Sorry for your loss during such a hard time. What a legend he was. X,' wrote another.</p>

<p>More to come </p>
